  131. let print_cmx_infos (ui, crc) =
  132.   print_general_infos
  133.     ui.ui_name crc ui.ui_defines ui.ui_imports_cmi ui.ui_imports_cmx;
  134.   begin match ui.ui_export_info with
  135.   | Clambda approx ->
  136.     if not !no_approx then begin
  137.       printf "Clambda approximation:\n";
  138.       Format.fprintf Format.std_formatter "  %a@." Printclambda.approx approx
  139.     end else
  140.       Format.printf "Clambda unit@.";
  141.   | Flambda export ->
  142.     if not !no_approx || not !no_code then
  143.       printf "Flambda export information:\n"
  144.     else
  145.       printf "Flambda unit\n";
  146.     if not !no_approx then begin
  147.       let cu =
  148.         Compilation_unit.create (Ident.create_persistent ui.ui_name)
  149.           (Linkage_name.create "__dummy__")
  150.       in
  151.       Compilation_unit.set_current cu;
  152.       let root_symbols =
  153.         List.map (fun s ->
  154.             Symbol.of_global_linkage cu (Linkage_name.create ("caml"^s)))
  155.           ui.ui_defines
  156.       in
  157.       Format.printf "approximations@ %a@.@."
  158.         Export_info.print_approx (export, root_symbols)
  159.     end;
  160.     if not !no_code then
  161.       Format.printf "functions@ %a@.@."
  162.         Export_info.print_functions export
  163.   end;

  208. ‌let dump_byte ic =

  211.   List.iter
  212.     (fun {Bytesections.name = section; len; _} ->
  213.        try

  215.            | CRCS ->

  217.                  Bytesections.read_section_struct toc ic section in
  218.                p_section "Imported units" imported_units
  219.            | DLLS ->

  221.                  Bytesections.read_section_string toc ic section
  222.                  |> Misc.split_null_terminated in

  224.            | DLPT ->

  226.                  Bytesections.read_section_string toc ic section

  228.                p_list "Additional DLL paths" print_line dll_paths
  229.            | PRIM ->
  230.                let prims =
  231.                  Bytesections.read_section_string toc ic section
  232.                  |> Misc.split_null_terminated in
  233.                p_list "Primitives used" print_line prims
  234.            | SYMB ->
  235.                let symb = Bytesections.read_section_struct toc ic section in
  236.                print_global_table symb
  237.            | _ -> ()
  238.        with _ -> ()
  239.     )
  240.     all

  252. ‌let exit_magic_msg msg =
  253.   exit_errf
  254.      "Wrong magic number:\n\
  255.       this tool only supports object files produced by compiler version\n\
  256.       \t%s\n\

  260. ‌let exit_magic_error ~expected_kind err =
  261.   exit_magic_msg Magic_number.(match err with
  262.     | Parse_error err -> explain_parse_error expected_kind err
  263.     | Unexpected_error err -> explain_unexpected_error err)

  265. (* assume that 'ic' is already positioned at the right place
  266.    depending on the format (usually right after the magic number,
  267.    but Exec and Cmxs differ) *)
  268. let dump_obj_by_kind filename ic obj_kind =
  269.   let open Magic_number in
  270.   match obj_kind with
  271.     | Cmo ->
  272. ‌       let cu_pos = input_binary_int ic in
  273.        seek_in ic cu_pos;
  274. ‌       let cu = (input_value ic : compilation_unit) in
  275.        close_in ic;
  276.        print_cmo_infos cu
  277.     | Cma ->
  278. ‌       let toc_pos = input_binary_int ic in
  279.        seek_in ic toc_pos;
  280. ‌       let toc = (input_value ic : library) in
  281.        close_in ic;
  282.        print_cma_infos toc
  283.     | Cmi | Cmt ->
  284.        close_in ic;
  285. ‌       let cmi, cmt = Cmt_format.read filename in
  286.        begin match cmi with
  287.          | None -> ()
  288.          | Some cmi ->
  289.             print_cmi_infos cmi.Cmi_format.cmi_name cmi.Cmi_format.cmi_crcs
  290.        end;
  291.        begin match cmt with
  292.          | None -> ()
  293.          | Some cmt -> print_cmt_infos cmt
  294.        end
  295.     | Cmx _config ->
  296. ‌       let ui = (input_value ic : unit_infos) in
  297. ‌       let crc = Digest.input ic in
  298.        close_in ic;
  299.        print_cmx_infos (ui, crc)
  300.     | Cmxa _config ->
  301. ‌       let li = (input_value ic : library_infos) in
  302.        close_in ic;
  303.        print_cmxa_infos li
  304.     | Exec ->
  305.        (* no assumptions on [ic] position,
  306.           [dump_byte] will seek at the right place *)
  307.        dump_byte ic;
  308.        close_in ic
  309.     | Cmxs ->
  310.        (* we assume we are at the offset of the dynamic information,
  311.           as returned by [find_dyn_offset]. *)
  312. ‌       let header = (input_value ic : dynheader) in
  313.        close_in ic;
  314.        print_cmxs_infos header;
  315.     | Ast_impl | Ast_intf ->
  316.        exit_errf "The object file type %S \
  317.                   is currently unsupported by this tool."
  318.          (human_name_of_kind obj_kind)

  320. ‌let dump_obj filename =
  321.   let open Magic_number in
  322.   let dump_standard ic =
  323.     match read_current_info ~expected_kind:None ic with
  324.       | Error ((Unexpected_error _) as err) ->
  325.          exit_magic_error ~expected_kind:None err
  326.       | Ok { kind; version = _ } ->
  327.          dump_obj_by_kind filename ic kind;
  328.          Ok ()
  329.       | Error (Parse_error head_error) ->
  330.          Error head_error
  331.   and dump_exec ic =
  332.     let pos_trailer = in_channel_length ic - Magic_number.magic_length in
  333.     let _ = seek_in ic pos_trailer in
  334.     let expected_kind = Some Exec in
  335.     match read_current_info ~expected_kind ic with
  336.       | Error ((Unexpected_error _) as err) ->
  337.          exit_magic_error ~expected_kind err
  338.       | Ok _ ->
  339.          dump_obj_by_kind filename ic Exec;
  340.          Ok ()
  341.       | Error (Parse_error _)  ->
  342.          Error ()
  343.   and dump_cmxs ic =
  344.     flush stdout;
  345.     match find_dyn_offset filename with
  346.       | None ->
  347.          exit_errf "Unable to read info on %s %s."
  348.            (human_name_of_kind Cmxs) filename
  349.       | Some offset ->
  350.          LargeFile.seek_in ic offset;
  351.          let header = (input_value ic : dynheader) in
  352.          let expected_kind = Some Cmxs in
  353.          match parse header.dynu_magic with
  354.            | Error err ->
  355.               exit_magic_error ~expected_kind (Parse_error err)
  356.            | Ok info ->
  357.          match check_current Cmxs info with
  358.            | Error err ->
  359.               exit_magic_error ~expected_kind (Unexpected_error err)
  360.            | Ok () ->
  361.          LargeFile.seek_in ic offset;
  362.          dump_obj_by_kind filename ic Cmxs;
  363.          ()
  364.   in
  365.   printf "File %s\n" filename;
  366.   let ic = open_in_bin filename in
  367.   match dump_standard ic with
  368.     | Ok () -> ()
  369.     | Error head_error ->
  370.   match dump_exec ic with
  371.     | Ok () -> ()
  372.     | Error () ->
  373.   if Filename.check_suffix filename ".cmxs"
  374.   then dump_cmxs ic
  375.   else exit_magic_error ~expected_kind:None (Parse_error head_error)
